<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <%= htmlWebpackPlugin.options.baseHeadContent %>

    <title><%= htmlWebpackPlugin.options.title %></title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="A two-octave digital piano written in Python."
    />
  </head>

  <body class="project-page">
    <%= htmlWebpackPlugin.options.preBodyContent %>

    <a class="home-link" href="/">Home</a>

    <div class="header">
      <div class="emoji">
        <span class="fluent-emoji--musical-keyboard"></span>
      </div>
      <h1><%= htmlWebpackPlugin.options.title %></h1>
    </div>

    <div class="content">
      <ul class="badge-list">
        <li>2016</li>
        <li>Python</li>
        <li>Tkinter</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        A two-octave digital piano, written in Python 3, that contains the
        following features:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li>Play using a mouse</li>
        <li>Play using the keyboard</li>
        <li>Recording</li>
        <li>Playback</li>
        <li>Preset songs</li>
      </ul>

      <img
        class="project-image lazy"
        data-src="<%= require('../../assets/projects/piano-711w.png') %>"
        alt="Python Piano"
        loading="lazy"
        width="300"
        height="88"
      />

      <h3>How to Play</h3>

      <p>
        To play the piano through keys on the keyboard, Z - M are the first
        octave white keys, and holding shift while pressing Z - M will play the
        second octave white keys. In the row of keys A - L, the keys that fall
        in between the "white" keys where the "black" keys would normally be are
        the sharp and flat keys. For example, because the key Z is the note C,
        the key S is the note C#.
      </p>

      <p>
        Source code in the
        <a href="https://github.com/JesseKuntz/my-piano" target="_blank"
          >Github repository</a
        >.
      </p>

      <p>
        I also re-wrote some of it in Preact, click
        <a href="https://preact-piano.netlify.app/" target="_blank">here ðŸŽ¹</a>
        to open a new tab and play it.
      </p>

      <p>
        All of the notes that are used I found on
        <a
          href="https://www.freesound.org/people/jobro/packs/2489/?page=1#sound"
          target="_blank"
          >Freesound</a
        >.
      </p>

      <p>
        All of the images that you see I created myself in
        <a href="http://www.picmonkey.com" target="_blank">PicMonkey</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <%= htmlWebpackPlugin.options.postBodyContent %>
  </body>
</html>
